# Preference Refinement — One Question at a Time

When the user is **refining design preferences**, **UI preferences**, or **other choices** (e.g. for the Iran War Chronicle site, or any “how do you want it?” style discussion):

1. **Ask one question at a time.** Use a single multiple-choice or yes/no question per turn.
2. **Wait for the user’s answer** before asking the next question.
3. **Do not list many questions in one message.** If you have several options to clarify, pick the most important one first, then continue with the next after the user replies.

This applies when the conversation is clearly about preference discovery or design refinement (e.g. “ask me questions to refine your understanding,” “what do I prefer for X?”). It does not override other rules (e.g. options menus in SCHOLAR/STATE) when those modes are active.

Reference: User request (Mar 2026) — one-at-a-time preference questions; Cursor rule to enforce it.
